*   Keys
Primary Key
It is a column (or a set of columns) in a table that uniquely identifies each row.(a unique id)
There is only 1PK & it should be NOT NULL

Foreign Key
A foreign key is a column (or a set of columns) in a table that refers to the primary key of another table
There can be multiple FK's
FKs can have duplicate and NULL values. 
